<br>
I've always loathed having port spells.  Yes, it is convienient to have them, so I can get around the world at my leisure.  No denying that.  I hate dealing with port/TL requests though.  Formerly, I used to be non-role; the idea of having to hide my class and level just to avoid getting port requests seemed silly, and I would just tell most people, &quot;I'm busy&quot;, or, reluctantly, &quot;come here and i'll port you&quot;.  I'll do ports if people offer money; I won't ask for it, and it's not a greed issue at all.  I still hate doing them, but if people are going to pay me money to have me port them, why not.  I still hate dealing with frequent and ceaseless TL requests however.<br>
<br>
So I gave up and went /role.  Nope- no help.  People either saw my familiar running haphazardly around the zone and knew there was a wizard near by, or saw the epic and thought &quot;hey, there are some spires right there! I bet they can port me to where I need to go!&quot;.  For those of you who tell people who don't like to port to put on /role, it doesn't help when you have your epic, SotW, or other trademark wizard items.  At least I can poof my familiar now without fear of getting corrupted... thankfully.<br>
<br>
So yesterday I started a new practice.  I just say &quot;no&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Can you port me to WC?&quot;<br>
&quot;No.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't have any money but can you port me to SF?&quot;<br>
&quot;No.&quot;<br>
<br>
It feels GREAT!  One word, and most people go away.  Some people react to this with shock.  One monk replied &quot;Well thanks a lot asshole!&quot;  I then told him why I was /role, how he shouldn't expect ports whenever he asked for them, and how I did not start a wizard to port his sorry ass around.  What he told me next almost shocked me.<br>
<br>
&quot;I didn't see it that way... I'm sorry.&quot;<br>
<br>
GASP!!!  Just saying no will be my motto from now on.  This has worked wonders for me.  I'll port my friends around- I, of course, will port myself around, and I'll still do ports if people are going to offer me money.  (And not the ambiguous &quot;I'll give you some money&quot;, because that, 90% of the time, translates to &quot;I'll give you 5pp&quot;.  Giving 5pp annoys me more than dealing with your tired melee ass in the first place.  The other 10% can learn to either state what they're giving or find another port.  Money isn't that important to me.)<br>
<br>
I am NOT a taxi.  I will never again offer an excuse as to why I won't port you; now, you will recieve a &quot;no&quot;, and you will LIKE it.<br>
<br>
To clerics who will post about not liking to do rezzes but doing them anyways- I offer 100pp for a rez, always.  If you don't want to rez me, fine, someone else will take my money.<br>
<br>
To druids- I normally despise you tree hugging hippies, but here I embrace you and suggest you try this out.  It's done wonders for my enjoyment of the game.<br>
<br>
I started a wizard to blow shit up.  This is how I shall play my wizard from now on.  Just say no!<br>
<br>
Claud Shadowflare<br>
60th Season Sorcerer of Ro<br>
